intro: Didymopanax venulosus, commonly known as the veiny sycamore, is a tropical tree native to South America. It belongs to the family Araliaceae and is characterized by its large, compound leaves with prominent venation. The plant typically grows in humid, lowland forests and can reach heights of up to 30 meters. Its bark is smooth and grayish, while its flowers are small and clustered in umbels. The fruit is a woody capsule that splits open to release seeds.
